article.headline: San Diego 81, Campbell 69
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Ross DeRogatis 27 points to lead San Diego in its 81-69 victory over Campbell Thursday. Gyno Pomare had 18 points and nine rebounds and made three blocked shots for San Diego (7-4), which won its fifth consecutive game. DeRogatis made 7-of-11 shots from the floor in the first half, including 6-for-10 from 3-point range. He finished making seven 3-pointers and was one point off his career high. Eric Smith led Campbell (3-4) with 13 points. Ruell Pringle added 12 points for the Flying Camels, which lost four straight games.
